GraphViz - Class in org.util.graphviz
Purpose: GraphViz Java API Description: With this Java class you can simply call dot from your Java programs Example usage: GraphViz gv = new GraphViz(); gv.addln(gv.start_graph()); gv.addln("A -> B;"); gv.addln("A -> C;"); gv.addln(gv.end_graph()); System.out.println(gv.getDotSource()); File out = new File("out.gif"); gv.writeGraphToFile(gv.getGraph(gv.getDotSource()), out);
GraphViz() - Constructor for class org.util.graphviz.GraphViz
Constructor: creates a new GraphViz object that will contain a graph.
